---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
	title="The Hermetic Flight: First Aerial Tarot Deck | Kickstarter Coming Soon"
	description="Experience tarot divination through embodied aerial arts. The world's first aerial tarot deck featuring 78 cards with 21 real aerialists."
>
	<!-- SEO Schema Slot -->
	<script type="application/ld+json" slot="head">
	{
	  "@context": "https://schema.org",
	  "@type": "Product",
	  "name": "The Hermetic Flight Aerial Tarot Deck",
	  "description": "The world's first aerial tarot deck combining divination with embodied aerial arts practice.",
	  "brand": { "@type": "Brand", "name": "The Hermetic Flight" },
	  "offers": {
		"@type": "Offer",
		"price": "65.00",
		"priceCurrency": "USD",
		"availability": "https://schema.org/PreOrder"
	  }
	}
	</script>

    <Header />

	<!-- HERO SECTION -->
	<div class="relative z-10 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-32 pb-24 flex flex-col items-center">
        
		<header class="text-center mb-20 animate-levitate-slow relative">
			<div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-32 h-32 bg-hermetic-gold/20 blur-[60px] rounded-full -z-10"></div>
			
			<div class="inline-block w-64 h-64 rounded-full overflow-hidden -mb-20 relative z-10">
				<img src="/images/logo.png" alt="The Hermetic Flight Logo" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
			</div>
			
			<h1 class="text-hermetic-gold font-serif font-bold text-4xl md:text-7xl tracking-[0.12em] uppercase drop-shadow-2xl mb-4 leading-tight">
				The Hermetic<br><span class="text-white mix-blend-overlay">Flight</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="text-hermetic-gold/60 font-serif text-xs md:text-sm tracking-[0.4em] uppercase border-t border-b border-hermetic-gold/20 py-3 inline-block">As Above, So Below</p>
		</header>

		<section class="glass-panel rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-14 text-center max-w-3xl reveal-up shadow-deep-glass">
			<h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-white mb-8 leading-snug">Welcome. <span class="text-hermetic-gold italic">We're thrilled you're here.</span></h2>
			<p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-200 font-light leading-relaxed mb-8">
				The Hermetic Flight is the world's first <strong class="text-hermetic-sulfur font-normal">aerial tarot deck</strong>—78 cards featuring 21 real aerial performers embodying the archetypes of tarot through movement.
			</p>
			<p class="text-base text-gray-400 font-light leading-relaxed border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/30 pl-6 mx-auto max-w-2xl text-left">
				"Between earth and sky, in that suspended moment where gravity releases its hold, we find the same liminal space that tarot divination has always occupied."
			</p>
		</section>
	</div>

	<!-- NEW SECTION: THE PROBLEM -->
	<div class="relative w-full bg-gradient-to-b from-hermetic-void via-hermetic-emerald/20 to-hermetic-void border-y border-hermetic-gold/10 backdrop-blur-sm z-10">
		<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
			
			<div class="text-center mb-20 reveal-up">
				<p class="font-serif text-hermetic-sulfur/60 text-sm tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-4">Five Years of Data Analyzed</p>
				<h3 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-white mb-6 leading-tight">The Tarot Community Has Been<br><span class="text-hermetic-gold italic">Vocal About These Frustrations</span></h3>
				<p class="text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg font-light leading-relaxed">
					After documenting thousands of discussions across Reddit, forums, and tarot communities, five common pain points emerged. <span class="text-white">We're listening...</span>
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Pain Point Grid -->
			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16">
				
				<!-- Pain 1: Overwhelm -->
				<div class="glass-panel p-8 rounded-xl reveal-up border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/40 hover:border-hermetic-gold transition duration-500">
					<div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
						<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-hermetic-void border border-hermetic-gold/50 flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-xl font-serif">1</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-hermetic-gold mt-1">"78 Cards Is Overwhelming"</h4>
					</div>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						Beginners report memorization anxiety as a major barrier to starting tarot. They abandon practice before gaining confidence, believing they need to memorize keywords before pulling their first card.
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-400 italic text-xs border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/20 pl-3">
						"78 cards to memorize? That's insane... I keep quitting before I even start." — Reddit user
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Pain 2: Court Cards -->
				<div class="glass-panel p-8 rounded-xl reveal-up border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/40 hover:border-hermetic-gold transition duration-500">
					<div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
						<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-hermetic-void border border-hermetic-gold/50 flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-xl font-serif">2</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-hermetic-gold mt-1">"Court Cards Are Often Confusing"</h4>
					</div>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						Many readers, even experienced ones, struggle with the 16 court cards. Traditional decks show similar-looking figures with crowns—Pages, Knights, Queens, and Kings blur together without distinct personalities.
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-400 italic text-xs border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/20 pl-3">
						"Most tarot decks don't show the personalities of court cards, so they're hard to tell apart." — The Simple Tarot
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Pain 3: Quality -->
				<div class="glass-panel p-8 rounded-xl reveal-up border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/40 hover:border-hermetic-gold transition duration-500">
					<div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
						<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-hermetic-void border border-hermetic-gold/50 flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-xl font-serif">3</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-hermetic-gold mt-1">"My Decks Keep Falling Apart"</h4>
					</div>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						Practitioners report consistent frustrations with card stock too thin to shuffle, oversized dimensions that hurt hands, flimsy packaging that disintegrates, and guidebooks offering only generic keywords.
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-400 italic text-xs border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/20 pl-3">
						"The very first thing I noticed was how terribly thin and poor quality the card stock is." — Amazon review
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Pain 4: Self-Reading -->
				<div class="glass-panel p-8 rounded-xl reveal-up border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/40 hover:border-hermetic-gold transition duration-500">
					<div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
						<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-hermetic-void border border-hermetic-gold/50 flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-xl font-serif">4</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-hermetic-gold mt-1">"I Can't Read Objectively for Myself"</h4>
					</div>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4">
						Many readers can interpret brilliantly for others but report difficulty with self-readings. Emotional investment clouds judgment, leading to wishful thinking and "convenient but highly subjective" interpretations.
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-400 italic text-xs border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/20 pl-3">
						"You end up with interpretations that match what you want to hear, not what you need to know." — Biddy Tarot
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Pain 5: Representation -->
				<div class="glass-panel p-8 rounded-xl reveal-up border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/40 hover:border-hermetic-gold transition duration-500 md:col-span-2">
					<div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
						<div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-hermetic-void border border-hermetic-gold/50 flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-xl font-serif">5</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-hermetic-gold mt-1">"I Don't See Myself in Traditional Decks"</h4>
					</div>
					<div class="md:flex gap-8 items-start">
						<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed text-sm mb-4 md:mb-0 md:flex-1">
							The RWS tradition presents homogeneous imagery—very white, very thin, very young. Practitioners actively seek decks featuring diverse body types, ages, ethnicities, abilities, and gender presentations, but finding both quality AND representation proves difficult.
						</p>
						<p class="text-gray-400 italic text-xs border-l-2 border-hermetic-gold/20 pl-3 md:w-80">
							"The traditional RWS is very white, very cis, very het, very ableist, very thin." — Asali Earthwork
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

			</div>

			<!-- Transition Statement -->
			<div class="text-center reveal-up">
				<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur font-serif text-lg tracking-wide">
					These problems have solutions.
				</p>
			</div>

		</div>
	</div>

	<!-- NEW SECTION: THE SOLUTION -->
	<div class="relative z-10 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-24">
		
		<div class="text-center mb-20 reveal-up">
			<p class="font-serif text-hermetic-sulfur/60 text-sm tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-4">Embodied Solutions</p>
			<h3 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-white mb-6 leading-tight">How <span class="text-hermetic-gold italic">Physical Embodiment</span><br>Solves These Challenges</h3>
		</div>

		<!-- Solutions Grid -->
		<div class="space-y-12">
			
			<!-- Solution 1: Visual Storytelling -->
			<div class="reveal-up">
				<div class="glass-panel p-10 md:p-12 rounded-xl max-w-4xl mx-auto">
					<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
						<div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-hermetic-gold/20 border border-hermetic-gold flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-sm font-serif">1</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-2xl text-hermetic-gold">Visual Storytelling Replaces Memorization</h4>
					</div>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-6 text-lg">
						When you see a performer suspended in The Strength card's intentional trust, you don't need to memorize "inner strength, courage, patience." The image tells the story. Your brain remembers bodies in motion—not abstract keywords.
					</p>
					<div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-black/40 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-hermetic-sulfur/40">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-hermetic-sulfur flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 font-light">
							<span class="text-white font-normal">Beginner-friendly:</span> Pull your first card without panic. The imagery shows you what you need to know.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Solution 2: Court Cards -->
			<div class="reveal-up">
				<div class="glass-panel p-10 md:p-12 rounded-xl max-w-4xl mx-auto">
					<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
						<div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-hermetic-gold/20 border border-hermetic-gold flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-sm font-serif">2</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-2xl text-hermetic-gold">Court Cards with Unmistakable Presence</h4>
					</div>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-6 text-lg">
						Knight energy literally moves with forward momentum—dynamic, risk-taking, action-oriented. Queen energy sits in grounded power—mastery, internal authority, magnetic presence. You don't guess at the difference. You see it in how bodies hold space.
					</p>
					<div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-black/40 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-hermetic-sulfur/40">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-hermetic-sulfur flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 font-light">
							<span class="text-white font-normal">Breakthrough moment:</span> After years of confusion, court cards finally click. Intermediates report mastery within 2-3 months.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Solution 3: Quality -->
			<div class="reveal-up">
				<div class="glass-panel p-10 md:p-12 rounded-xl max-w-4xl mx-auto">
					<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
						<div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-hermetic-gold/20 border border-hermetic-gold flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-sm font-serif">3</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-2xl text-hermetic-gold">Premium Materials for Daily Practice</h4>
					</div>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4 text-lg">
						Your practice deserves tools that last. We addressed every documented quality complaint:
					</p>
					<ul class="space-y-3 mb-6">
						<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-gray-300 text-sm">
							<span class="text-hermetic-sulfur mt-1">◆</span>
							<span><strong class="text-white">300-350 GSM card stock</strong> with matte linen finish—substantial without excessive stiffness</span>
						</li>
						<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-gray-300 text-sm">
							<span class="text-hermetic-sulfur mt-1">◆</span>
							<span><strong class="text-white">Standard 2.75" × 4.75" sizing</strong>—comfortable for all hand sizes, easy to shuffle</span>
						</li>
						<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-gray-300 text-sm">
							<span class="text-hermetic-sulfur mt-1">◆</span>
							<span><strong class="text-white">custom rigid 2-piece box</strong>—survives years of daily openings</span>
						</li>
						<li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-gray-300 text-sm">
							<span class="text-hermetic-sulfur mt-1">◆</span>
							<span><strong class="text-white">Comprehensive guidebook</strong>—deck-specific meanings, not generic keywords</span>
						</li>
					</ul>
					<div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-black/40 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-hermetic-sulfur/40">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-hermetic-sulfur flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 font-light">
							<span class="text-white font-normal">Built to last:</span> Daily use for years. Cards still look pristine. Packaging still secure.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Solution 4: Grounded Imagery -->
			<div class="reveal-up">
				<div class="glass-panel p-10 md:p-12 rounded-xl max-w-4xl mx-auto">
					<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
						<div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-hermetic-gold/20 border border-hermetic-gold flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-sm font-serif">4</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-2xl text-hermetic-gold">Grounded Imagery for Self-Reading</h4>
					</div>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed mb-6 text-lg">
						Clear, specific visual stories reduce projection when reading for yourself. You can't make a suspended inversion mean something it doesn't. Physical bodies anchor abstract concepts, helping you stay honest when emotions run high.
					</p>
					<div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-black/40 rounded-lg border-l-2 border-hermetic-sulfur/40">
						<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-hermetic-sulfur flex-shrink-0 mt-1" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 font-light">
							<span class="text-white font-normal">Objectivity support:</span> Guidebook includes self-reading techniques from five years of community research.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- Solution 5: Representation -->
			<div class="reveal-up">
				<div class="glass-panel p-12 md:p-14 rounded-xl border-hermetic-gold/40 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
					<div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8 justify-center">
						<div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-hermetic-gold/20 border border-hermetic-gold flex items-center justify-center text-hermetic-gold text-sm font-serif">5</div>
						<h4 class="font-serif text-3xl text-hermetic-gold">Authentic Diverse Representation</h4>
					</div>
					<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
						<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed text-lg mb-8 text-center">
							The 21 aerial performers who embody these archetypes represent the actual diversity of aerial arts communities—various body types, ages, ethnicities, and gender presentations. This isn't tokenism. This is documentation of real humans doing real aerial work.
						</p>
						<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
							<div class="text-center p-6 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-hermetic-gold/20">
								<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur text-3xl font-serif mb-2">21</p>
								<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Professional Performers</p>
							</div>
							<div class="text-center p-6 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-hermetic-gold/20">
								<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur text-3xl font-serif mb-2">78</p>
								<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Choreographed Cards</p>
							</div>
							<div class="text-center p-6 bg-black/30 rounded-lg border border-hermetic-gold/20">
								<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur text-3xl font-serif mb-2">0%</p>
								<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">AI-Generated Art</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

		</div>
	</div>

	<!-- SECTION: WHO THIS IS FOR -->
	<div class="relative w-full bg-gradient-to-r from-hermetic-void via-hermetic-emerald/40 to-hermetic-void border-y border-hermetic-gold/20 backdrop-blur-sm z-10">
		<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 reveal-up">
			<h3 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl text-white mb-16">This Deck Is For You If...</h3>
			
			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
				<div class="glass-panel p-6 rounded-lg text-center hover:border-hermetic-gold/60 transition duration-500">
					<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur font-serif text-4xl mb-3">✦</p>
					<h4 class="text-white font-serif text-lg mb-3">You're Overwhelmed</h4>
					<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm font-light">78 cards feels impossible and you need visual stories, not memorization requirements</p>
				</div>
				<div class="glass-panel p-6 rounded-lg text-center hover:border-hermetic-gold/60 transition duration-500">
					<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur font-serif text-4xl mb-3">✦</p>
					<h4 class="text-white font-serif text-lg mb-3">You're Stuck</h4>
					<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm font-light">Court cards still confuse you after years and you need embodied imagery to break through</p>
				</div>
				<div class="glass-panel p-6 rounded-lg text-center hover:border-hermetic-gold/60 transition duration-500">
					<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur font-serif text-4xl mb-3">✦</p>
					<h4 class="text-white font-serif text-lg mb-3">You Value Quality</h4>
					<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm font-light">You're tired of decks falling apart and want premium materials with diverse representation</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
				<div class="glass-panel p-6 rounded-lg text-center hover:border-hermetic-gold/60 transition duration-500">
					<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur font-serif text-4xl mb-3">✦</p>
					<h4 class="text-white font-serif text-lg mb-3">You're Professional</h4>
					<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm font-light">You need tools that justify your rates and become part of your practice identity</p>
				</div>
				<div class="glass-panel p-6 rounded-lg text-center hover:border-hermetic-gold/60 transition duration-500">
					<p class="text-hermetic-sulfur font-serif text-4xl mb-3">✦</p>
					<h4 class="text-white font-serif text-lg mb-3">You're Curious</h4>
					<p class="text-gray-400 text-sm font-light">You want to explore tarot without pressure, expertise requirements, or mystical gatekeeping</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<!-- SECTION: DISCOVER YOUR ARCHETYPE -->
	<div class="relative z-10 max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 text-center reveal-up">
		<p class="font-serif text-hermetic-sulfur text-sm tracking-[0.3em] uppercase mb-4">Discover Your Archetype</p>
		<h3 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-white mb-8 leading-tight">How Does <span class="text-hermetic-gold italic">Tarot Speak to You?</span></h3>
		<p class="text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg font-light leading-relaxed mb-6">
			Every tarot practitioner has a natural lens; a way of receiving wisdom that feels like home. Some need to see the structure before they trust it. Others feel truth in their body before their mind catches up. Some seek depth in the shadows. Others flow with creative intuition.
		</p>
		<p class="text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-lg font-light leading-relaxed mb-6">
			We've identified six distinct archetypes that shape how people connect with tarot. Knowing yours transforms everything: how you learn, which cards speak loudest, and why certain decks have never quite fit.
		</p>
		<p class="text-hermetic-gold max-w-xl mx-auto font-serif tracking-wide italic">
			Twenty questions. Five minutes. One revelation about how you're wired.
		</p>
	</div>

	<!-- SECTION: SIX PATHS THROUGH THE CARDS -->
	<div class="relative w-full bg-gradient-to-b from-hermetic-void via-hermetic-emerald/20 to-hermetic-void border-y border-hermetic-gold/10 backdrop-blur-sm z-10">
		<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
			<div class="text-center mb-20 reveal-up">
				<h3 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-white mb-6">6 Paths Through The Cards: <span class="text-hermetic-gold italic">Which Will You Take?</span></h3>
			</div>

			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 reveal-up">
				<!-- Archetype 1 -->
				<div class="glass-panel p-8 rounded-xl hover:border-hermetic-gold/60 transition duration-500">
					<h4 class="font-serif text-xl text-hermetic-gold mb-4">✦ The Air Weaver</h4>
					<p class="text-gray-300 font-light leading-relaxed text-sm">
						You hunt for patterns in chaos. Structure is how you breathe. You need to see the blueprint before you trust the building.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Archetype 2 -->
